{"word":"Διόθεν","slug":"Διόθεν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Διόθεν</b></el>  (Dio/qen) adverb<p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>Διός</el>, <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> of <a href='S:Ζεύς'><el>Ζεύς</el></a>\n<p/><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>sent from Zeus, by his will</i> or <i>favour</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/>"}]}